What happened internally?

Docker read instructions line by line.

Each instruction created a new layer.


t asma-file
craete the tag name image, image name = asma-file
tag = latest


. (dot)

Very important interview question.

Means:

Current folder is the build context, Docker sends all files from current folder to Docker daemon.


Difference between RUN and CMD?

Very important.

Human answer:

RUN	CMD
Executes during image build	Executes when container starts

Example:

RUN installs curl
CMD prints message

Container stops because the main process finished execution. In this case echo command completed and container exited.

Docker uses layers for caching, faster builds, and storage optimization.